commentTextItems.html: and that's the game!, tossed, on off, turning away, Williams leans forward, unfurls a reverse sweep over point to the rope. Zimbabwe are back in the series

commentPostTextItems.html: That will be all from us today , let's join again on Sunday for the final ODI. It promises to be a thriller. Cheers
Chris Mpofu is the Man of the match

Zimbabwe have leveled the series, Mire and Moor provided the solid foundation with an opening stand of 79. That was followed by a mini collapse losing 2 wickets inside 7 balls. Williams and Moor 4th wicket stand saw out the remaining runs with ease. Spinners R Khan and M Nabi took the three wickets.

dismissalComment.html: GONE! length, outside off, Shaidi goes after it, gets a tiny top edge , Moor collect in front of his face.

dismissalText.commentary: Samiullah Shinwari c Chatara b Cremer 13 (31b 1x4 0x6 32m) SR: 41.93

dismissalComment.html: good running catch!, tossed on leg, Shinwari comes forward, unfurls the sweep shot, takes off the top edge, flies wide to the right of Chatara who runs back from short fine to grab it

dismissalText.commentary: Karim Janat c †Moor b Cremer 9 (33b 0x4 0x6 53m) SR: 27.27

dismissalComment.html: Moor takes another one!, tossed on off, Karim Janat leans forward for a drive, gets beaten for turn and pace, gets a thick outside edge into the keeper's gloves

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi c Ervine b Mire 17 (31b 1x4 0x6 37m) SR: 54.83

dismissalComment.html: gone! back of a length, on off, Nabi gets back and is squared, the ball takes the leading edge, pops up straight to Ervine at point

dismissalText.commentary: Gulbadin Naib run out (Waller/Williams) 10 (28b 0x4 0x6 35m) SR: 35.71

dismissalComment.html: oh What have they done there!, tossed, on off, pushed towards Waller at cover, Naib wants a single and takes off, gets sent back, Waller fields , rolls it under arm to Williams who whips off the bails

stories.seoTitle: Zimbabwe draw level as Afghanistan misfire again
